The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Air-India defends plane pact

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, May 11: Air-India (A-I) has termed the allegations made by Airbus Industrie regarding the plan to acquire aircraft from Boeing as unwarranted and uncalled for.

 A-I has written a letter, strongly protesting against the remarks that attributed motives behind the national carriers recent plan to acquire 50 aircraft. 

 An Airbus official had accused A-I of wrongly evaluating the specifications of two aircraft makers, which is worth over $6 billion.

 We take strong exceptions as these allegations are completely baseless and uncalled for, Air-India chairman V. Thulasidas said. 

 Air-India is a reputed and well-established international carrier and have adequate experience and exposure to evaluate aircraft and decide what is best, he added. 




